NOVEMBER 19‚Äì22, 2020
EPIC STORYTELLING IMAGE
MASTERCLASS WITH MU PAN

In this masterclass with grandmaster @mupan1911 you will delve into the world of epic storytelling images. Looking at the epic work through history, such as Tibetan tanka, Flemish master pieces, Indian miniature painting, or Japanese nishiki-E with their grand, epic compositions, battle scenes, dramatic actions, and large groups of multiple figures, you will explore the traditions and analyze the design strategies used by the old masters. Using only simple materials‚Äîpaper, drawing supplies and aqueous media (watercolor, gouache, acrylic)‚Äîyou will then reinvent your own modern masterpiece with storytelling, and create an epic image on any kind of subject you prefer, based on your own influences from art history, literature, film, myth, and even fantasy. 
If you dare, get your ticket for this epic adventure. Just follow link in bio. .

JUNE 11‚Äì14, 2020
ILLUSTRATION MASTERCLASS
WITH HARRY CAMPBELL:
THE IDEA OF YOU. IT'S PERSONAL

Original ideas, genuinely personal and unique solutions come from within‚Äîmeaning from who you are, what you are, how you feel, what you like, how you think. At best, ideas in some way reflect who you are. Your own unique way of seeing and solving a problem, interpreting a narrative, or simply augmenting a beautiful or thoughtfully written editorial ... This 4 day masterclass with Harry Campbell is all about generating solutions to problems in a very personal way. 
Eary Bird Ticket sales starts now, just follow link in bio.
